- Microsoft Windows Driver Samples SimpleMediaSource sample
  - Used as the starting point for the Windows Frame Server custom media source.
  - License notice is preserved in native/vendor/MICROSOFT-WINDOWS-DRIVER-SAMPLES-LICENSE.txt.

- Microsoft Windows Implementation Library (WIL)
  - Vendored under native/vendor/wil.
  - License notice is preserved in native/vendor/wil/LICENSE.

- Android Debug Bridge and Windows ADB DLLs
  - Bundled under phonecam/bin for USB device detection and adb reverse.
  - Distributed as Android platform-tools components. Release packaging must record
    the exact platform-tools version and source URL used.

- scrcpy runtime files and dependencies
  - Bundled under phonecam/bin from the previous v1 implementation.
  - The v2 Android companion path does not depend on scrcpy for the main camera
    feed. Before public release, either remove these files or document exact
    versions, source URLs, and licenses for scrcpy, FFmpeg DLLs, SDL, and libusb.

- pywebview, pystray, Pillow, PyInstaller
  - Python dependencies listed in phonecam/requirements.txt.
  - Release packaging must include dependency versions and licenses.

Generated artifacts are not source and should not be committed:
PhoneCam.exe, PhoneCamCompanion.apk, MSI packages, native x64/Release outputs,
catalog files, build directories, pycache files, and local certificates.
